{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SelectionModelRef"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This support is then used by widgets using list models to add the ability"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to select and unselect various items."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GTK provides default implementations of the most common selection modes such"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as [class"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.SingleSelection"},{"type":"text","text":"], so you will only need to implement this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interface if you want detailed control about how selections should be handled."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSelectionModel"},{"type":"text","text":" supports a single boolean per item indicating if an item is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"selected or not. This can be queried via [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.SelectionModel.is_selected"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When the selected state of one or more items changes, the model will emit the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[signal"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.SelectionModel::selection-changed"},{"type":"text","text":"] signal by calling the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.SelectionModel.selection_changed"},{"type":"text","text":"] function. The positions given"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in that signal may have their selection state changed, though that is not a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requirement. If new items added to the model via the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[signal"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ListModel::items-changed"},{"type":"text","text":"] signal are selected or not is up to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implementation."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that items added via [signal"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ListModel::items-changed"},{"type":"text","text":"] may already"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be selected and no [signal"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.SelectionModel::selection-changed"},{"type":"text","text":"] will be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"emitted for them. So to track which items are selected, it is necessary to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"listen to both signals."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Additionally, the interface can expose functionality to select and unselect"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"items. If these functions are implemented, GTKâ€™s list widgets will allow users"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to select and unselect items. However, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSelectionModel"},{"type":"text","text":"s are free to only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implement them partially or not at all. In that case the widgets will not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"support the unimplemented operations."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When selecting or unselecting is supported by a model, the return values of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the selection functions do "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not"}]},{"type":"text","text":" indicate if selection or unselection happened."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"They are only meant to indicate complete failure, like when this mode of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"selecting is not supported by the model."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Selections may happen asynchronously, so the only reliable way to find out"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when an item was selected is to listen to the signals that indicate selection."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SelectionModelRef"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSelectionModel"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SelectionModelProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SelectionModelRef"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSelectionModel"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gtk\/selectionmodelref"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gtk\/3GIO17ListModelProtocolP","doc:\/\/Gtk\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SelectionModelProtocol"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SelectionModelRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSelectionModel"},{"type":"text","text":" is an interface that add support for selection to list models."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragme